        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-10-11T19:33:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, this might have been the key---I tried to use this method earlier, but the thread join was before the channel stops, so any thread that is waiting would make the joins fail.\n\nNow, I\u0027m switching the order of channel stopping and thread joining, and am calling it before any DLL unloading is done, so it should work much better now.\n\nBTW, rendererimpl destructor (which was another potential path to call stop) is not called frequently enough. I think it is because it is a smart pointer and it only goes away when all render threads do, but the original problem is that the render threads don\u0027t go away soon enough.",
      "parentUuid": "df9654c8_5607142b",
